comments:
Knowledge: New understanding of warfare from at least three perspectives: biological, cultural, and archaeological. Definitions of war, its origins, its development and changes, peacemaking and after facts of war; 

Skills: Making connections between readings, discussions, and lectures; sometimes working specifically on refutations and critique of academic writing, but also using the class reading to analyze documentaries;

Insights: I think the course really provided a ~depth~ of perspective for looking at the origins and developments of warfare
